National Bank of Kenya Says First-Half Profit Declines 22%

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-08-03T12:45:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/national-bank-of-kenya-says-first-half-profit-declines-22-1-.html
National Bank of Kenya Ltd. (NBKL) , a state-
owned lender, said profit fell 22 percent in the first half
through June compared with a year earlier.  Net income declined to 640.3 million shillings ($7 million)
from 816.3 million shillings a year earlier, the company said in
an e-mailed statement today.  Net interest income, the money banks make from loans,
increased to 2.67 billion shillings from 2.25 billion shillings,
National Bank said.  The shares of NBK, as the lender is known, declined the
most since July 29, losing 1.7 percent to 28.75 shillings by the
3 p.m. close in Nairobi, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net . 